{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-5465].
  {panel}

Renaming a page creates a new version of the page. But people who are notified about the change get confused when they try to figure out what has changed, and the page comparison view indicates "0 changes".

For example using the {tip} macro, the behaviour can be demonstrated as follows.

Line breaks before or after the {tip} macro creates empty lines in the tip box. For example:
   {tip}
   Text text text
   {tip}

Will create blank lines before and after the content ("Text text text")

Using:
    {tip}Text text text{tip}

the tip box is displayed without the blank lines. 

This would not be a problem if Confluence would not re-format the markup to be  
   {tip}
   Text text text
   {tip}

no matter how it was written initially.

