What would be really useful is to see, when we assign Groups to Users, the list of Spaces that this user will be able to see.

It is often very cumbersome to log in as a specific user to see if we effectively haven't limited or opened too much the rights for him.

I got an error when I was switching between the wiki markup to rich text editors.
I think it was related to the use of "+" with the underline and italic formatting.

In general, the following markup entered on the markup page:
{noformat}_+aaa+_\+_+bbb+_\+_+ccc+_{noformat}
is shown correctly on the rich text page (underlined italic letters), but a switch back to the markup page mutilates the markup to:
{noformat}_+aaa+_+_+bbb+_+_+ccc+_{noformat}
which then shows incorrectly on the rich text page as all underlined italic (including "+").
Yet another switch back to the markup page shows the following:
{noformat}_+aaa+__+\+bbb+__+\+ccc+_{noformat}
